description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a versatile and enthusiastic qualified clinical photographer to join our busy team providing a comprehensive photography and video service to the Cardiff and Vale University Health Board . Based primarily at the University Hospital of Wales but with major commitments to University Hospital Llandough, the department delivers a fast, high-quality clinical and non-clinical service to a wide range of clients using digital photography and video technology. Our major users include ophthamology, dermatology, wound healing and the breast care team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be highly motivated, conscientious, a quick learner and a good communicator. You must be able to work alone as well as being a committed team player. The successful candidate will have a good range of clinical photography skills, (studio and location based) and have the strong desire to develop their knowledge and skills even further, the department supports and encourages development of its staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is part-time (30 hours per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff and Vale University Local Health Board is the largest Health Board in Wales and one of the largest in the UK. It provides healthcare to a population of around 500,000 people in the Cardiff and Vale area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris Tetley Head of Clinical Photography&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Christopher.Tetley@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 02920743308&lt;/p&gt;
